Given A = {1, 2, 3, 4} and B = {4, 5, 6, 7}
A - B set will contain those elements which are present in A but not in B.
we can see A $\cap$ B = {4}
Now A - B = A - (A $\cap$ B)
So A - B = {1, 2, 3, 4} - {4} = {1, 2, 3}

